<subSubSection id="C35552F7FF96BF3EA599487841621E8B" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF0017CFF96BF3EA599487841621E8B" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF96BF3EA599487843581E18" bold="true" box="[199,324,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Comment.</emphasis>
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF96BF3EA7DD487F41301E18" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[643,812,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biaculeatum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF96BF3EA7DD487F41301E18" box="[643,812,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">L. biaculeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F35841ECFF96BF3EA129487846A61E18" box="[1143,1210,331,357]" name="Nepal" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Nepal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF96BF3EA197487847421E18" author="Assing, V." box="[1225,1374,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">Assing 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF96BF3EA4C7485C43F61EF4" box="[409,490,367,393]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Xizang</collectingRegion>
are very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF96BF3EA79D484346181EF4" authority="Assing, 2012" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[707,1028,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biaculeatum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF96BF3EA79D484341771EF4" box="[707,875,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">L. biaculeatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF96BF3EA62E485C46181EF4" author="Assing, V." box="[880,1028,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">
Assing, 
<quantity id="4CB7AC99FF96BF3EA692485C46181EF4" box="[972,1028,367,393]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11048" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" unit="in" value="2012.0">2012</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance (Fig. 2A) and aedeagal characters (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF96BF3EA42148A043DF1ED0" box="[383,451,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[478,1114,527,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-142@2.[471,1117,525,1739]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lobrathium biaculeatum. A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scales: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 4. Lobrathium chengzhifeii. A male sternite VII B male sternite VIII C aedeagus in ventral view D aedeagus in lateral view. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The only difference found is a more acute ventral process of aedeagus. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF96BF3EA5E8488B43421EAC" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[182,350,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biaculeatum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF96BF3EA5E8488B43421EAC" box="[182,350,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">L. biaculeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF96BF3EA4D1488440371EAC" author="Assing, V." box="[399,555,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">Assing (2012</bibRefCitation>
: figure 109–112). Therefore, we consider it to belong to the same species. The above record from 
<collectingCountry id="F35841ECFF96BF3EA43348E843AC1E88" box="[365,432,475,501]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">China</collectingCountry>
represents a new country record (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF96BF3EA67248E8416C1E8B" box="[812,880,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 5–8" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1007,1031]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,416,984]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[415,1173,416,984]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5–8. Collecting sites. 5 habitats of Lobrathium anatinum in Guangxi 6 habitats of Lobrathium biaculeatum in Xizang 7 type locality of Lobrathium chengzhifeii 8 habitats of Lobrathium excisissimum in Xizang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524312/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
